Date: Mon 3 Mar 2003
From: Scott Simpson <SSimpson@mr.peacecorps.gov>

Mauritania: Outbreak of Crimean-Congo Hemorrhagic Fever in the Capital
--------------------------------------------------
An outbreak of Crimean-Congo hemorrhagic fever has been documented in
Nouakchott, the capital of Mauritania. In total, there have been 19
cases and 5 deaths. The index case was detected on 18 Feb 2003. The
last new case was identified on 28 Feb 2003.
--
Scott Simpson
Medical Officer
Peace Corps Mauritania
<SSimpson@mr.peacecorps.gov>
[Crimean-Congo hemorrhagic fever has been reported in the past few
years from many countries in Asia, Europe, the Middle East, and South
Africa (see below). This is the first recent report of the disease
from northern Africa. - Mod.CP]
